  "description": [
    "Friday 21 February 1958 Happiness Editors Note Thin in a re sumption of the articles started in the spring which had to be de layed due to unforeseen events Preventive Medicine In the earlier articles under tins title we covered accidents and diseases which could occur during the summertime and how to prevent them Remember the old saying that An ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure Well it may surpise many of you to learn that a branch of tlie Medical Department is de voted to spotting trouble before disease occurs or to find out why it occurs when it does not only in the summertime but on a year around basis For the first of this group of articles I would like to tell you about this branch and some of the problems studied In the following articles we will go into greater detail as to the main problems which effect you and your environment Tiie Environmental Sanitation Department as it is more com monly called operates under the Medical Officer with CWO Don ald Sabin as Preventive Medicine Officer lie is assisted by two technicians John S McCullough lIM2 and Kenneth King HM2 v horn"
  ],
